			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<span class="time"><strong>Saviors of the Paragon</strong></span>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#606B73" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Been a kind of group effort @ <a href="http://www.clashofsteel.com" target="_blank">www.clashofsteel.com</a>  Decided to post it here to share it with you all.  Updates will come as they are written, any feedback is greatly appreciated :&gt;<br />
<br />
Chapter 1: Blood and Brew <br />
<br />
The rain outside pounded at the roof of the Tavern. The patrons of the Lions Mane Inn in Qeynos were all drinking the night away. The storms had caused most of the boats heading out of Qeynos to be in port for the night. The barmaids scurried in and out of the room gathering up dishes and alcohol and replacing it with more. The night had worn on and Relik the warrior had grown tired of the human town. He reminisced about when he was young in Halas when he used to disappear for days in the Everfrost peaks, honing his skills on polar bear cubs, ice goblins, and eventually the great woolly mammoths. He relished the solitude, the invigorating, cold clear air and the pristine beauty of the snowy mountains. A far cry from where he finds himself of late, waiting on orders for his next assignment in the fight against the growing menace of unspeakable evil spreading from the very bowels of Norrath. <br />
<br />
Relik had only just arrived in Qeynos a few days prior. The elders of Halas had received a summons to send some of their finest warriors to aid in a battle that would surely determine the very fate of Norrath. The elders had told him about the summons but had not heard what he was here for. Eager to see the face of battle once again the Warrior accepted his mission and had made his way to Qeynos where he would meet up with the rest of the summoned. Days had now passed and rumors of higher than average amounts of undead had been spreading across the land like wildfire. Relik was tired of waiting, and if he did not hear word by the end of the night he was ready to travel back home. <br />
<br />
&quot;Warriors aren't made for sitting..&quot; Relik quietly grumbled to himself. <br />
<br />
&quot;But when the time comes, it is the patience and determination that can win the war&quot; said a female voice. <br />
<br />
Relik spun around in his seat and before him stood a most striking vision, a combination of feminine beauty and the strength of steel. Attired in ranger garb, the lovely wood elf appraised Relik with piercing blue eyes. She ran a hand through her close-cropped red hair and murmured softly, &quot;Tunare weeps and rages.&quot; She stared at him expectantly, waiting for the correct reply to the coded greeting. <br />
<br />
&quot;I live and die to avenge her suffering,&quot; replied Relik immediately. <br />
<br />
Some tension appeared to leave the ranger's taut frame. &quot;My name is Nasu, and I have been sent to bring you to the meeting place where we will be given our orders. The defense of our world is about to commence.&quot; <br />
<br />
Relik stood and bowed before Nasu. &quot;I am Relik and at your service, ma'am. I am ready to depart immediately.&quot; <br />
<br />
Nasu smiled wryly. &quot;So I gathered. Follow me.&quot; <br />
<br />
They wound their way among the tavern patrons, heading for the door, when suddenly a dagger whisked by Relik's head. Relik turned to see three dark cloaked figures. Relik yelled, &quot; Who dares?! &quot; as he unsheathed his swords. <br />
<br />
Nasu stepped forwards past Relik with the dagger in hand. Fear, anger, and hatred lined her voice as she closed with the enemy &quot; They are ...... the Teir'Dal.... Dark elves in your tongue &quot; <br />
<br />
Relik's stance hid his fear well.... he had heard stories of these ones.... bad stories. <br />
<br />
At that moment the 3 dark figures lunged towards the two companions with sickly green fire emanating from the raised hands of the one farthest away. Relik felt a nauseating heat rising inside of him, making him stumble. All of a sudden, the evil assailants stopped short, as if the floor reached up and grabbed their feet. Almost immediately, they were bathed in a fiery red glow and began screaming in agony. Relik charged ahead despite his pain, swords flashing menacingly. As he reached his foes, he felt a healing wave and a powerful surge of strength come over him. With a fierce Halas war cry, he swung his weapons in a swift flurry that left the helpless Tier'dal lying in bloody heaps. <br />
<br />
The inn was deafeningly silent. The patrons stood frozen in place with looks of disbelief and horror on their faces. It was surely the first time many of them had ever seen an evil dark elf and they clearly did not enjoy the event. <br />
<br />
Nasu looked down at the remains of their attackers disdainfully. &quot;Certainly not the best example of what we will be up against. The enemy is far more powerful than these wretched creatures demonstrated. Perhaps they are trying to make us feel over-confident or perhaps it was just meant as a warning. Whatever the reason, we have been discovered! We must make haste before it is too late!&quot; <br />
<br />
They rushed out into the storm, With Nasu silently praying that if the others of their cause had met with similar attacks, they had fared no worse than Relik and she had.</div>
